ol.li:
If the destination of the packet is a direct neighbor, e.g., installed
by IPv6 Neighbor Discovery, then the packet MUST be
forwarded to that neighbor;

Else If the destination of the packet is an indirect neighbor, e.g.,
installed by a multicast DAO message from a common neighbor,
see , then the packet MUST be forwarded to the common neighbor;

Else, if there is a RIB entry for the same Track (e.g., installed by an
SM-VIO in a DAO message with the destination as target), and the next hop in
the RIB entry is a direct neighbor, then the packet is passed to that neighbor;
